<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880610-0164 </DOCNO><HL> Amex Option Trading Begins on Handamp;R Block, Symbol Technologies </HL><SO> </SO><CO> HRB SBL FBH FLP </CO><IN> SCR STK </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   The American Stock Exchange said it began trading put and call options on Handamp;R Block Inc. and Symbol Technologies Inc. common stock.    They replace the common of Frank B. Hall andamp; Co. and Floating Point Systems Inc.    The initial expiration months on the options are July, October and January. Handamp;R Block, based in Kansas City, Mo., sells tax preparation services. Bohemia, N.Y.-based Symbol Technologies makes laser bar-code scanner equipment.    Options give a holder the right, but not the obligation, to buy or sell a security at a specified price within a limited period.    In New York Stock Exchange trading yesterday, Handamp;R Block closed at $27.25, down 62.5 cents, and Symbol Technologies closed at $25.875, up 37.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>